Boot configurations**\\n\\nI need to figure out adding the spring-aop dependency without specifying a version, which might fail. Using Gradle and Spring Boot BOM could work if I add the platform for dependencies. The command looks like adding `testImplementation platform(\\\"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-dependencies:$libraryVersion\\\")`, followed by necessary Spring Boot dependencies.\\n\\nI wonder if it’s okay to skip spring-boot-test and just use `AnnotationConfigApplicationContext`. I also need to ensure I’m evaluating conditions correctly, which may require manual setups instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing custom PEP conditions**\\n\\nI'm looking into testing a custom PEP with a missing bean condition. First, I want to register PersistenceExceptionTranslationAutoConfiguration and refresh the context to check if the bean is a proxy target class. \\n\\nNext, I'll disable the property to see if no beans are of type PEP. Then I’ll tweak the proxy property and confirm that PEP is indeed not a proxy target class. Finally, I'll check if I need a custom PEP and ensure that the EntityScan configurations are correctly set up.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xv8yS4YLbFDqLxzroHhIalFu|fc_0bfbf52b8adbe95c016a0d4124aaa8819ea7247bc4610a3f21", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-autoconfigure/4.0.6/*/spring-boot-autoconfigure-4.0.6.jar -v org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfiguration | grep -A40 RuntimeVisibleAnnotations"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 942, "output": 1635, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33809, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779253519158, "responseId": "resp_0bfbf52b8adbe95c016a0d410fa264819e979a8b48ca9ac071"}}
